  "texts": [
    "For example, Iu and Wong (2023) asked ChatGPT to prepare cross-examination questions for a case and draft a skeleton argument based on analysis of a complex fact pattern, among other tasks.",
    "They did not prompt the model or evaluate their results in a systematic way.",
    "They did, however, suggest ChatGPT performed well at this task, though not as well as a lawyer.",
    "These authors also used ChatGPT to assist them in drafting their papers.",
    "In terms of the particular LLMs tested, three studies (Bommarito II and Katz 2022; Savelka 2023; Blair-Stanek et al. 2023) used text-davinci-003, as we do in answering our first research question."
